<section id="content-paragraphs" class="content-section">
  <div class="section-container">

    <h2 class="section-heading">Key Contributions</h2>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <p class="intro-text">
      We evaluate <em>Sense-Think-Act</em> in agentic AI robots, with Connected and Autonomous Vehicles (CAVs) as a safety-critical testbed. This setting combines high-rate camera/LiDAR streams, strict compute and memory limits, vibration-induced sensing artifacts, and real-time planning demands. Success in this domain demonstrates how freshness-driven sensor-to-decision adaptation can support broader resource-constrained robotic systems.
    </p>

    <!-- Cards -->
    <div class="contribution-grid">

      <!-- Card 1 -->
      <div class="contribution-card">
        <div class="icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor">
            <path d="M13 2L3 14h7l-1 8 10-12h-7z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Freshness-Driven Stream Refinement</h3>
        <p>
          A vibration- and context-aware admission-control policy selectively drops, reduces, or fully processes camera frames and LiDAR scans. It combines visual/geometric change, cached semantic risk cues, runtime pressure, reinforcement learning, and safety overrides to improve decision-time freshness while preserving safety-critical evidence.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 2 -->
      <div class="contribution-card">
        <div class="icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor">
            <ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3"/>
            <path d="M3 5v6c0 1.66 4.03 3 9 3s9-1.34 9-3V5"/>
            <path d="M3 11v6c0 1.66 4.03 3 9 3s9-1.34 9-3v-6"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Failure-Aligned Evidence Capsules</h3>
        <p>
          Instead of routine logging, <em>Sense-Think-Act</em> monitors sustained perception degradation and stores compact pre-event, during-event, and post-event multimodal evidence. These capsules focus storage on failure-relevant data for efficient continual retraining.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 3 -->
      <div class="contribution-card">
        <div class="icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor">
            <polyline points="3 17 9 11 13 15 21 7"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Real-World Freshness-to-Action Gains</h3>
        <p>
          Across V2X-Radar and a physical RovaX robot, <em>Sense-Think-Act</em> reduces planner update delay by up to <strong>70.5%</strong>, preserves up to <strong>99.3%</strong> of safety-critical inputs, and improves closed-loop navigation success by up to <strong>30%</strong> in real-world trials.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

